    <question>
        <prompt>William Doak's deportation campaigns primarily targeted:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">European immigrants</option>
            <option letter="b">Mexican and Mexican-American residents</option>
            <option letter="c">Asian immigrants</option>
            <option letter="d">Political activists</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>As Hoover's Secretary of Labor, William Doak's deportation campaigns primarily targeted Mexican and Mexican-American residents during the early Depression years. Claiming this would create jobs for American citizens, his actions led to the forced repatriation of hundreds of thousands of people of Mexican descent, including many U.S. citizens, reflecting the era's xenophobia and economic nationalism.</explanation>
